# Base the custom model on your existing local Gemma 4 12B install
FROM gemma4:12b

# --- RESOURCE & CONTEXT ADJUSTMENTS ---
# Sets context window to 16k (forces Ollama to allocate system RAM/VRAM safely)
PARAMETER num_ctx 16384
# Reserve thread count for CPU offloading processing
PARAMETER num_thread 8

# --- SAMPLING CONTROLS (Tuned for strict JSON schema extraction) ---
# Slightly cooler than default to prevent creative formatting/hallucinations
PARAMETER temperature 0.3
PARAMETER top_p 0.95
PARAMETER top_k 64

# --- AGENTIC SYSTEM OVERRIDES ---
SYSTEM """You are a senior software engineer acting as an autonomous terminal agent.
- Your PRIMARY objective is to execute tasks sequentially.
- NEVER search the web or external URLs for configuration variables that are expected to exist in local files (like CLAUDE.md). Always read local workspace files first.
- If a tool call fails, analyze the standard error output, adjust your parameter values, and attempt a logical correction. Do not repeat the exact failed call.
- Keep output formats structured, concise, and clean.
"""